data.title: Parker says, "Give it a try, you'll really like it."
data.text: Not fancy, with basic ambiance, but the food is totally delicious.  The entire family seems to be in on the action, from waiter/waitress staff to servers to cooks.  Study the menu, there are a large number of really excellent dishes there.  We shared pork, beef, garlic rice and noodles, plus some dumplings for an appetizer.  The food was wonderfully prepared with great presentation..........and the staff was incredibly friendly.  Check it out.

data.title: Another average Filipino food
data.text: It was good years ago but lately their food became subpar.  The one in Jersey City is no better.  Not sure what happened to their food but the people that worked their were friendly.
